For more details, please refer to the Phyluce documentation: Phyluce Assembly Tutorial https://phyluce.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/tutorial-1.html#assemble-the-data

Step-by-Step Instructions
1. Create a Directory for Logs

To store log files, first create a directory named log:

bash
Copy code
mkdir log

2. Prepare the assembly.conf Configuration File

The assembly.conf file should list all the species and their corresponding directories. Hereâ€™s an example structure for this file:

ini
Copy code
